      "data": {
        "body": "Goal: Make Twilite's authoring contract explicit and durable\nStatus: open\n\nTasks in scope:\n1. Make the contract executable\n2. Strengthen authoring-boundary diagnostics\n3. Sharpen primitive selection and create-time guidance\n4. Turn tutorials into authoritative specimens\n5. Harden GitHub and persistence state reporting\n\nOpen questions:\n1. Which authoring failures should be hard errors first?\n2. How much legacy tolerance should remain?",
        "status": "open",
        "owner": "Michael",
        "priority": "critical",
        "estimateHours": "12",
        "acceptanceCriteria": [
          "The app explains contract failures precisely at the point of mistake",
          "Canonical specimens cover the common declaration, port, portal, and summary patterns",
          "Models can author valid graphs without relying on tribal knowledge"
